 changed to a semi-weekly publication cycle in 1902 and appears to have ceased with volume 11, number 2 on December 30, 1904.  The index includes all available local news items, and advertisements for local businesses are included."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-03-24T08:50:23.920Z", "group": ["catalog-split-15", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-15"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2015451931", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["nodaway county", "missouri", "skidmore"], "number": ["n907934049", "2015451931", "2024-03-22t19:13:16"], "original_format": ["book"], "partof": ["catalog"], "score": 12.225493, "shelf_id": "AI21 .S6 2013", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["nodaway county", "indexes", "skidmore (mo.)", "american newspapers", "skidmore", "skidmore standard", "missouri", "nodaway county (mo.)", "genealogy", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2024-03-24T08:52:02.875Z", "title": "Index to the Skidmore Standard", "type": ["text"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2015451931"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2024846916", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024846916/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/66c0d9fa-f47b-5eff-8668-18edd553299c", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.law/llserialsetce.02656_00_00-002-0060-0000", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/llserialsetce.02656_00_00-002-0060-0000/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["united states congress. house", "united states. government publishing office", "united states. war department", "united states. congress. house"], "date": "1889", "dates": ["1889"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-07-17T06:58:51.332Z", "group": ["catalog-split-10", "catalog", "ll/llserialset/mono", "main-catalog-split-10", "congressional-serial-set-document-level"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024846916/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ll/llserialsetce/02/65/6_/00/_0/0/02656_00_00/02656_00_00-002-0060-0000/0011.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ll/llserialsetce/02/65/6_/00/_0/0/02656_00_00/02656_00_00-002-0060-0000/0011.gif#h=150&w=93", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ll:llserialsetce:02:65:6_:00:_0:0:02656_00_00:02656_00_00-002-0060-0000:0011/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=431&w=267", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ll:llserialsetce:02:65:6_:00:_0:0:02656_00_00:02656_00_00-002-0060-0000:0011/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=862&w=535", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ll:llserialsetce:02:65:6_:00:_0:0:02656_00_00:02656_00_00-002-0060-0000:0011/full/pct:50/0/default.jpg#h=1725&w=1070", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ll:llserialsetce:02:65:6_:00:_0:0:02656_00_00:02656_00_00-002-0060-0000:0011/full/pct:100/0/default.jpg#h=3450&w=2140"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["arkansas", "little rock", "lawrence", "virginia", "united states", "kansas", "missouri"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "application/pdf", "text/plain", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2026-07-16t23:18:09.400000", "2025-03-21t15:33:34", "2024846916", "online resource"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["book"], "other_title": ["Cited as: H. Misc. Doc. 50-60"], "partof": ["united states congressional serial set: serial no. 2656", "50th congress, 2nd session", "united states congressional serial set (bound house and senate documents and reports)", "law library of congress", "catalog"], "score": 11.965567, "shelf_id": "KF12", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["recruiting and enlistment", "arkansas", "slaves", "guerrilla warfare", "campaigns", "united states", "contraband of war", "massacres", "little rock (ark.)", "lawrence massacre, lawrence, kan", "strategy", "19th century", "lawrence (kan.)", "national guard", "virginia", "legislative materials", "missouri", "ordnance", "trading with the enemy", "civil war", "government publication", "habeas corpus", "marmaduke, john sappington", "military occupation", "indians", "military hospitals", "militia", "military bases", "military art and science", "military supplies", "history", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-07-17T08:38:57.093Z", "title": "War of the Rebellion: A Compilation of the Official Records of the Union and Confederate Armies. [Trans-Mississippi Theater: Advance on Little Rock/Prairie Grove Campaign/Quantrill's Raid/Marmaduke's Expeditions into Missouri; January-December 1863; Series 1, Vol. 22, Chapter 34, Part 2]", "type": ["text"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024846916/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/app/item/2008661333/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2008661333/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2008661333/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/cph.3b35981", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/cph.3b35981/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2008661333"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["robinson, henry r."], "date": "1839-01-01", "dates": ["1839"], "description": ["1 print : lithograph with watercolor, on wove paper ; 24 x 33.1 cm. (image) | A portrayal of Treasury Secretary Levi Woodbury as a hen nurturing corruption and shielding New York City customs house officials from congressional scrutiny.  Woodbury spreads his wings over several chicks pecking at gold coins beneath him, as two of the chicks swim off toward Liverpool. The foremost one represents former Collector of the Port Samuel Swartwout, found to have defrauded the government of nearly $1.25 million. The second is federal district attorney William M. Price, a coconspirator. Both fled to England. (See \"Price Current\" and \"Sub Treasurers Meeting in England,\" nos. 1838-21 and -20.)  Woodbury is threatened by a hawk, \"Committee of Investigations,\" with the head of Kentucky congressman James Harlan, who flies overhead calling, \"I'll have you! hen & all.\" Harlan was chairman of the House committee established in January 1839 to probe the Swartwout defalcations. The hen cries: \"Hawk! . . . run! . . . Fly Sam [Swartwout] & Bill [Price]! take to the water--quick, before he comes! dive or he'll get you! . . . Here Hoyty [i.e., Swartwout's successor Jesse Hoyt]! hide between my legs! . . . hide Ogden! run Phillips! fly Fleming! come Gratiot! Hawk Boydy! . . . Linn! Scud Harris! Fly Spencer! Drop gold & run all! come under! . . .I'll cover you!\""], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T22:55:14.546Z", "group": ["app", "catalog-split-00", "catalog", "american-cartoon-prints", "main-catalog-split-00", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2008661333/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/cph/3b30000/3b35000/3b35900/3b35981_150px.jpg#h=106&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/cph/3b30000/3b35000/3b35900/3b35981t.gif#h=106&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/cph/3b30000/3b35000/3b35900/3b35981r.jpg#h=454&w=640"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["2013-06-04t10:28:21", "http://www.loc.gov/item/app1994000068/pp", "2008661333", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2008661333"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["cartoon prints, american", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "prints and photographs division", "catalog"], "score": 11.824439, "shelf_id": "PC/US - 1839.R661, no. 12 (A size) [P&P]", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["boyd", "hoyt, jesse", "political cartoons", "harlan, james", "lithographs", "ogden", "house", "linn", "united states", "fleming", "congress", "phillips", "spencer", "harris", "gratiot"], "timestamp": "2022-04-23T06:13:11.199Z", "title": "The treasury-hen alarmed", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2008661333/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sanborn04733_001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gmd/g4164lm.g4164lm_g047331885", "http://www.loc.go